debrief.itemText: Please answer the following questions about your experience. Click and drag the red scrollbar to move down. Do not leave any box blank. Type ‘no’ or ‘n/a’ if you don’t have a response.
Briefly describe what you were asked to do in this experiment? (if there is existing text in the box delete it.
debrief.response: In the first part, I chose between two shapes presented to me out of four possible (circle, triangle, hexagon, star), which would give me 1 or 10 points, the goal being to get as many points as possible. The shapes each had their own probability to give 10 points. In the second part, I described either a number as higher or lower than 153 or a letter as closer to A or Z, while alternating which selection I would choose. In the last part, I did the same as the second part but with the added points of the shapes telling me how likely I was to get 10 points if I got it right, but certain shapes imposed a time limit that if exceeded would net me 0 points.
